OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1777302667
OL,3,CFuneral held for baby found under
OL,4,Cfloorboards during renovation
OL,6,FAt an inquest opening earlier this
OL,7,Fmonth, senior coroner Jeremy
OL,8,FChipperfield was told DNA was unable
OL,9,Fto identify the infant but did reveal
OL,10,Fthat the baby was a boy.
OL,12,FThe inquest heard the baby boy could
OL,13,Fhave even lived up to 300 years ago.
OL,15,FOne type of radio-carbon dating
OL,16,Frevealed that the baby was born before
OL,17,Fthe first atomic bomb tests in New
OL,18,FMexico on June 16 1945, the inquest
OL,19,Fheard.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1777302667
OL,3,CFuneral held for baby found under
OL,4,Cfloorboards during renovation
OL,6,FAnother type of radio-carbon dating
OL,7,Findicated a range of possible dates
OL,8,Fthat the baby lived as between 1726
OL,9,Fand 1812.
OL,11,FCllr Cathy Hunt, Durham County
OL,12,FCouncil's cabinet member for children
OL,13,Fand young people's services, said:
OL,14,F"Sadly, for reasons we will never
OL,15,Fknow, this little boy was never given
OL,16,Fthe dignified and appropriate burial
OL,17,Fhe deserved, so it was important that
OL,18,Fhe was laid to rest in a way that
OL,19,Fhonoured a life that could have been.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,422,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F421A1777302667
OL,3,CFuneral held for baby found under
OL,4,Cfloorboards during renovation
OL,6,F"We'd like to thank everyone who
OL,7,Fattended today's funeral and we hope
OL,8,FBaby Auckland can now restJin peace."
OL,10,FDuring the service, Assistant Chief
OL,11,FConstable Jon McAdam, alongside
OL,12,Fpartners, laid flowers inJremembrance.
OL,14,FThe inquest into the circumstances
OL,15,Fsurrounding the death will continue on
OL,16,F18 May in Crook, CountyJDurham.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/8
